        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add tool search directory mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add `tools.toolSearch.mode: \"directory\"` so large catalogs can expose a compact prompt directory plus `tool_describe`/`tool_call` controls while deferring most schemas.\n- Hydrate likely or requested directory tools from the catalog, including missing tool calls, while preserving sequential execution contracts.\n- Keep client tools directly visible in directory mode and document the new mode.\n\nFork attribution: based on JuanHuaXu/openclaw `codex/tool-search-directory-mode`, compared from `codex/fix-post-tool-continuation-guard`.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts src/agents/tool-search.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.tool-search-run-plan.test.ts src/config/schema.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Behavior or issue addressed: `tools.toolSearch.mode: \"directory\"` keeps hidden catalog tool schemas deferred while still letting the agent loop hydrate and execute a requested catalog tool through `resolveMissingTool`.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS with Node 24.16.0 after `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`, running the PR branch at `35198cf38b`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran `node --import tsx --input-type=module -` with a throwaway stdin proof script importing `applyToolSchemaDirectoryCatalog`, `buildToolSchemaDirectoryPrompt`, `resolveToolSearchCatalogTool`, and `runAgentLoop`. The script created a directory-mode catalog with `tool_describe`, `tool_call`, one hydrated likely tool, and one deferred hidden tool, then made the model emit a hidden-tool call so `resolveMissingTool` had to hydrate it before execution.\n- Evidence after fix:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"directory\",\n  \"compacted\": true,\n  \"catalogToolCount\": 2,\n  \"visibleToolsBeforeModel\": [\n    \"tool_describe\",\n    \"tool_call\",\n    \"proof_visible_memory\"\n  ],\n  \"visibleToolsAfterHydration\": [\n    \"tool_describe\",\n    \"tool_call\",\n    \"proof_visible_memory\",\n    \"proof_hidden_weather\"\n  ],\n  \"directoryPromptHasHiddenTool\": true,\n  \"hiddenToolDirectlyVisibleInitially\": false,\n  \"hiddenToolCalls\": 1,\n  \"finalAssistantText\": \"Directory proof complete.\"\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: Directory mode compacted the catalog; the hidden weather tool appeared in the directory prompt but was not initially exposed as a provider-visible schema, then `resolveMissingTool` hydrated `proof_hidden_weather` and the real agent loop executed it once before producing the final assistant response.\n- What was not tested: No live provider API call, packaged install, MCP server, or channel delivery path was exercised in this proof; the focused checks above cover the changed unit/runtime/config surfaces.\n",
